The paper discusses novel techniques and data structures for efficient decision making in various domains, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on multidimensional data structures and queries indicates that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions applications in business and economics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CE (Computational Economics). The use of these techniques for decision making also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
